Lillie CRAWFORD, Executrix of the Estate of J. A. Crawford, Deceased, v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE. No. 7709. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 11, 1938. L. A. Luce, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. James W. Morris, Asst. Atty. Gen., for respondent.

Before PUCKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal in this case be and the same is dismissed pursuant to stipulation of counsel.
